  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The book, \"Comics of the New Europe,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2023, explores the cultural and artistic dimensions of comic art in the European context, representing a significant contribution to the field.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">\"Comics of the New Europe,\" published in 2023 by Leuven University Press, positions itself as a vital exploration of the evolving landscape of comic art across Europe. This publication offers a comprehensive examination of the cultural significance, artistic diversity, and the historical context of comics within various European societies.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While specific metrics on citations and community engagement are currently absent, the work's existence within a reputable academic publisher underscores its potential for future scholarly impact. The publication from Leuven University Press is expected to engage both academic circles and enthusiasts of comic art, though it will take time for its influence to materialize in citation counts and community discourse.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Notably, the absence of specific online mentions or community discussions indicates that the book is yet to make its mark in public or academic dialogues. This baseline suggests a starting point for the authors' engagement with the community, allowing for growth and interaction as readers begin to discover and disseminate its insights.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The authors' commitment to furthering knowledge in this niche field is reflected in the selection of Leuven University Press as the publishing venue, known for its dedication to quality academic publications. Moving forward, increased visibility and scholarly engagement could foster discussions around the themes presented in the book, contributing to a deeper understanding of comics as an integral part of cultural heritage in the new European context.</p>",
